  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "cryptsetup security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for cryptsetup is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "cryptsetup is a utility used to conveniently set up disk encryption based on the DMCrypt kernel module.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nIt was found that a specially crafted LUKS header could trick cryptsetup into disabling encryption during the recovery of the device. An attacker with physical access to the medium, such as a flash disk, could use this flaw to force a user into permanently disabling the encryption layer of that medium.(CVE-2021-4122)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for cryptsetup is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2 and openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "cryptsetup",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
